# Model Selection Guide

## Model Tiers

| Tier | Model | Input/Output Cost | Best For |
|------|-------|-------------------|----------|
| **Tier 1 - Premium** | Claude 4.6 Opus | $5 / $25 per MTok | Deep reasoning, architecture, security analysis, code review |
| **Tier 2 - Balanced** | Claude 4.5 Sonnet | $3 / $15 per MTok | Code implementation, following plans, interactive refinement |
| **Tier 3 - Fast** | Gemini 3 Flash | ~$0.50 / $3 per MTok | Procedural tasks, validation, exploration, simple queries |

## Command Recommendations

| Command | Tier | Model | Why |
|---------|------|-------|-----|
| `/implementation/plan-feature` | 1 | Opus | Deep codebase analysis and architectural planning |
| `/implementation/implement` | 1 | Opus | Orchestration requires reasoning about state and delegation |
| `/code-review/review-pr` | 1 | Opus | Security analysis, pattern recognition, nuanced feedback |
| `/implementation/execute` | 2 | Sonnet | Following detailed plans, writing code to spec |
| `/code-review/interactive-review` | 2 | Sonnet | Conversational refinement of existing review |
| `/git/commit` | 2 | Sonnet | Analyzing changes and crafting commit messages |
| `/git/squash` | 2 | Sonnet | Branch analysis and commit grouping |
| `/implementation/validate` | 3 | Fast | Running commands and reporting results |

## Subagent Recommendations

| Agent | Tier | Task `model` param | Why |
|-------|------|-------------------|-----|
| `planner` | 1 | _(default)_ | Deep analysis, plan generation |
| `executor` | 2 | _(default)_ | Code implementation from plan |
| `validator` | 3 | `"fast"` | Procedural validation commands |
| `reviewer` | 1 | _(default)_ | Autonomous PR review, deep code analysis |
| `squasher` | 2 | _(default)_ | Branch analysis, strategy selection |

## Important Notes

- **Commands run at the user's selected model** -- these recommendations are guidance for the UI dropdown
- **The Task tool's `model` parameter only accepts `"fast"`** -- you cannot specify exact model names
- **Default Task model is the current conversation model** -- omit `model` param for Tier 1/2 tasks
- **Use `model: "fast"` only for Tier 3 tasks** like validation and exploration
- **When in doubt, use Tier 2** -- it balances cost and capability well
